{"TopicId":213270,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"My idea for procedural fuel tank construction","CreatedByName":"FishInferno","CreatedById":106219,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T17:50:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"FishInferno","CreatedById":106219,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T17:50:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe procedural wings are a huge step forward for KSP, and procedural radiators/solar panels have also been teased during the dev updates. At this point, I think procedural fuel tanks make a lot of sense and would be an easy way to reduce part counts. I also really like the new hydrogen tank style and think that other fuel types should be available for them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022h7rzourklkka1.jpg?width=640\u0026amp;crop=smart\u0026amp;a\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022162.81\u0022 height=\u00221042\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://preview.redd.it/h7rzourklkka1.jpg?width=640\u0026amp;crop=smart\u0026amp;auto=webp\u0026amp;v=enabled\u0026amp;s=5fdb185c590736b035782bf7577c81e2519612a0\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"CyberSiren","CreatedById":226504,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T19:37:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProcedural fuel tanks would be\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheOtherDave","CreatedById":32305,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T03:38:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019m hugely in favor of this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-27T03:39:18Z\u0022 title=\u002202/27/2023 03:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 27, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by TheOtherDave\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"brygun","CreatedById":141392,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T11:52:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdd that fuel tanks could also be set as crew space. There are real world plans to do this. This could be done in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E. Ideally engineers could do the conversion of space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI often used tanks to give more crew volume to simulate better living conditions then sitting in one\u0027s own sweat for a 2 year mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daniel Prates","CreatedById":172769,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T15:00:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0would be able to finally retire!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T19:25:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224246072\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677510050\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172769\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Daniel Prates\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Daniel Prates said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022187168\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/187168-lisias/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Lisias\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0would be able to finally retire!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnlikely. There\u0027re also gears, lights, and lots of other things in need to be scaled! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Daniel Prates","CreatedById":172769,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-27T22:39:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224246430\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022213270\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677525920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnlikely. There\u0027re also gears, lights, and lots of other things in need to be scaled! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re a trooper!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GigFiz","CreatedById":205457,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-28T00:42:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fuel tank part section is definitely a magnet for tons of unnecessary clutter. I posted a similar idea to this in the last few months, though I didn\u0027t have the bit about the trusses. The additional thought I\u0027ll from that is that even if they don\u0027t want to give us 100% granular control of tank size, they should still do it this way and just make the minimum increment step much larger. Heck, even if they weren\u0027t procedural at all, it would still declutter the part list a lot to have just one entry per diameter/type combo on the list, and let you change the length in the build space, or have it so when you click the fuel tank in the part list, you then get a quick pop up menu to select the size.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}